            . I am in the employ of Thomas Shelton, an <rs id="t18271025-253-viclabel1447" type="occupation">oilman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-253-victim1310 t18271025-253-viclabel1447"></join>, of Lisson-grove, North. Last Saturday morning, between ten and eleven o'clock, I left my barrow and basket at the corner of <placeName id="t18271025-253-crimeloc1448">South-bank</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-253-crimeloc1448" type="placeName" value="South-bank"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-253-crimeloc1448" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-253-off1445 t18271025-253-crimeloc1448"></join>, with wood and candles in it. I went to a house, and on returning, the basket and candles were gone: I saw the prisoner about a dozen yards off - I ran after him, and took him with the candles in his hand - he had moved the barrow about twelve yards, and then taken the basket out.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-253-person1312">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BETTY
               <interp inst="t18271025-253-person1312" type="surname" value="BETTY"></interp>
