                     <interp inst="t18271025-253-person1312" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was at the corner of the street, and saw the prisoner move the barrow, and then take the basket; he came towards me; I took hold of him, and asked what he was going to do; he said to take it to a man - he could not tell me who; he had wheeled the barrow about seventy yards.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A gentleman told me to move it out of the way of his gig.</p>
